# W-Buildings-Tab-UI — DONE 2026-05-01

Three commits, one concern each. SPEC §9 + HD source `scr_02` honored.

## Commits

| Concern | Hash    | Files touched                                                      |
|---------|---------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| A       | ea9fea1 | `js/forge/forge-render.js`                                          |
| B       | a2c49a9 | `js/forge/forge-render.js`, `forge-buildings.js`, `forge-daily.js`, `js/core/wg-state.js` |
| C       | (this)  | `js/core/wg-state.js`, `js/forge/forge-craft.js`, `STATE_OF_BUILD.md`, this marker |

## UI elements shipped (per scr_02 reference)

- **Diorama (~30vh canvas)** — procedurally drawn cave + pagoda + animated
  campfire with two-frequency flicker (4.7 Hz + 9.2 Hz). Tier-shaped pagoda
  roof grows with level; campfire flame scales with level.
- **Power readout** — `Power: <N>` in red/orange centered below diorama
  (`#ff8838` with text-shadow glow).
- **8-slot building grid (4×2)** — Cave / Forge / Campfire unlocked + Fence /
  Cannon / Anvil / Range / Trap locked; tap unlocked = detail modal, tap
  locked = unlock-flow modal.
- **Building detail modal** — 5-row upgrade ladder (next 5 levels) with
  cost + benefit per tier, primary Upgrade button.
- **Daily Chest with 7-day streak strip** — pip row of days (current
  day glowing, claimed days dimmed); reward count-up animation on claim
  (700 ms ease-out cubic); day 7 hands out a guaranteed Rare relic.
- **Forge anvil station** — anvil glyph on stone-platform shape; tap →
  polished crafting modal with Craft × 10 + ⓘ Probability Info + material
  display + disabled state when fragments / daily cap insufficient.
- **Locked-slot unlock flow** — GS gate readout (orange when not met),
  standard unlock (only when GS met), 200💎 bypass, Watch Ad bypass via
  `WG.Ads.showRewardedVideo`.
- **Polish** — tap scale-bounce on every button; `modal-pop` 200 ms keyframe
  animation (already in index.html); reward count-up; diorama rAF stops
  when Forge tab loses focus.

## Tunables (all inline at the top of their respective modules)

`forge-buildings.js`:
- `DIAMOND_BYPASS_COST = 200`
- `AD_REWARD_AVAILABLE = true`
- `DEFS[*].unlockGS` — 500 / 1500 / 3000 / 6000 / 10000 (Fence / Cannon /
  Anvil / Range / Trap)
- `DEFS[*].unlockCost` — coins/diamonds resource cost once GS gate is met
- `DEFS.cave.baseGen = 0.6` (idle coin trickle)

`forge-daily.js`:
- `DAY_MS = 24 h` (cooldown)
- `STREAK_GRACE_MS = 48 h` (skip threshold — beyond this, streak resets)
- `STREAK_REWARDS[7]` — coin / diamond / card / fragment ladder
- Day 7 sets `rareRelicChance: true` → guaranteed Rare relic drop

`forge-craft.js`:
- Drop probabilities at Forge Lv.1: Common 70% / Rare 22% / Epic 6% /
  Legendary 1.8% / Mythic 0.2% (visible in Probability Info modal).
  Each Forge level shifts ~2.5% from Common into higher tiers.
- `craftDailyMax = 10` batches/day
- `costPerBatch = 30 fragments`

`forge-render.js`:
- `DIORAMA_HEIGHT_VH = 30`
- `DIORAMA_FLICKER_HZ_PRIMARY = 4.7`, `_OVERTONE = 9.2`

## Power formula update (Concern C)

`WG.State.recomputePower()` — buildings now contribute `level × 50`
(previously `level × 6`).  Default-state Power moved 76 → 208, in line
with scr_02's mid-tier 1347.

## Verified in browser smoke test (localhost:3996)

- Forge tab renders all 5 sections (h2, diorama canvas, Power readout,
  buildings section with chest + grid, anvil section).
- Locked-slot tap on Fence opens modal showing "Unlock at Power 500
  (you: 208)" in orange + Watch Ad + Pay 200💎 + Cancel.
- Craft × 10 button opens crafting modal; Probability Info nested modal
  shows Common 70.0% / Rare 22.0% / Epic 6.0% / Legendary 1.8% / Mythic
  0.2% at Forge Lv.1.
- Daily Chest claim → reward modal with count-up animation; streak day
  advances; pip strip updates next refresh.
- Diorama canvas animates campfire flicker; rAF stops on tab change.
- All 4 module files pass `node --check`.

## Constraints honored

- DOM-based UI throughout — diorama canvas is decorative only, every tap
  target is a real DOM element. Reliable phone taps.
- One concern per commit. Three commits.
- Polish mandate satisfied: modal pop-in (CSS keyframe), reward count-up
  (rAF), tap scale-bounce on every button.
- Probability table baseline matches the spec's 70/22/6/1.8/0.2.
